original_title: Sri Lanka to strengthen relations with China’s Yunnan province
original_body_lines: ECONOMYNEXT – Sri Lanka’s cabinet of minister had approved the singing of a memorandum to strengthen economic
and cultural relations with China’s Yunnan province, a government statement said.
The MoU will be signed between the External Resources Department of Sri Lanka and the foreign affairs office
The agreement will expand co-operation in tourism, economic, market, commercial, agricultural, community
The agreement is to be signed when Yunnan Provincial Governor Wang Yubo visits Sri Lanka from May 16 to 20.
